Small correction (VERY IMPORTANT)

Actually text should NOT be cached, only the prompt template should.

So the true professional version is this:

@lru_cache
def load_prompt_template():

    client = Client(
        base_url=PHOENIX_ENDPOINT,
        api_key=PHOENIX_API_KEY
    )

    prompt = client.prompts.get(
        prompt_version_id="UHJv"
    )

    prompt_messages = prompt._template["messages"]

    system_prompt = next(

        (
            item["content"][0]["text"]
            for item in prompt_messages
            if item.get("role") == "system"
        ),

        None
    )

    return system_prompt



def get_final_prompt(text:str)->str:

    system_prompt = load_prompt_template()

    return system_prompt.format(
        text=text
    )

This is the correct enterprise design.

Why?

Because:
	•	Template rarely changes → cache
	•	Text always changes → don’t cache

This is how Microsoft PromptFlow / LangChain prompt registries are structured.

